java -version

sudo apt install fontconfig openjdk-17-jre

Java --version 


Go to firefox and typw download Jenkins > click on first link > download and deploy >scrool 
and click on ubuntu and Debian > copy the links and paste it in terminal. 
Download and add the repository key so that your system trusts the Jenkins packages: 

sudo wget -O /usr/share/keyrings/jenkins-keyring.asc   https://pkg.jenkins.io/debian
stable/jenkins.io-2023.key


Add the Jenkins repository to your system’s sources list: 

echo "deb [signed-by=/usr/share/keyrings/jenkins-keyring.asc]" 
https://pkg.jenkins.io/debian-stable binary/ | sudo tee   
/etc/apt/sources.list.d/jenkins.list > /dev/null 


sudo apt update

sudo apt-get install Jenkins

sudo systemctl start jenkins 

sudo systemctl status jenkins 


Open web browser. 

Navigate to: http://localhost:8080 

Unlock Jenkins: The initial Jenkins screen will ask for an administrator password. 
Retrieve it by running: 

sudo more /var/lib/jenkins/secrets/initialAdminPassword


5. Follow the Setup Wizard:   
o Install Suggested Plugins: Click on “Install suggested plugins” for a typical setup.  
o Create an Admin User: Follow prompts to create your first admin user.  
o Finalize Configuration: Complete the remaining setup steps.

sudo apt-get remove purge jenkins 
